ravenewcode-affiliate-program-tips-an-interview-with-jean-galea-of-wp-mayor/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 13 Aug 2012 22:09:37 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Affiliates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Journal\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"affiliate\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"WPtouch\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"http://www.bravenewcode.com/?p=9566\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:332:\"We recently took some time to catch up with BraveNewCode Affiliate Program member, Jean Galea at his home in sunny Malta. Those who keep up with WordPress news and reviews may be familiar with Jean who participates regularly in the WordPress community as the creator of WordPress resource site, WPMayor. We asked Jean to share [...]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Joyce Peralta\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5211:\"<p><a href=\"http://www.bravenewcode.com/2012/08/bravenewcode-affiliate-program-tips-an-interview-with-jean-galea-of-wp-mayor/allnighter-jean-600/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10370\"><img src=\"http://www.bravenewcode.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/allnighter-jean-600.png\" alt=\"Jean Galea of WPMayor\" title=\"allnighter-jean-600\" width=\"600\" height=\"319\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-10370\" /></a></p>\n<p>We recently took some time to catch up with <a title=\"Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://www.bravenewcode.com/affiliate-program/\">BraveNewCode Affiliate Program</a> member, Jean Galea at his home in sunny Malta. Those who keep up with WordPress news and reviews may be familiar with Jean who participates regularly in the WordPress community as the creator of WordPress resource site, <a title=\"WP Mayor\" href=\"http://www.wpmayor.com/\">WPMayor</a>.</p>\n<p>We asked Jean to share some of his thoughts on WordPress and tips for other BNC Affiliate Program participants. Check out his responses below.</p>\n<p><strong>Why do you work with WordPress?</strong><br />\nWordPress is hands-down the most user-friendly CMS I&#8217;ve come across since I started working on the web more than 10 years ago. It&#8217;s also one of the easiest to extend and build upon. That means that both clients and developers are happy using it. Not to mention that with the millions of websites running WordPress, there is a huge market for WordPress developers like me, and a fun community to hang out in.</p>\n<p><strong>What&#8217;s your favourite thing about WordPress?</strong><br />\nI&#8217;d have to say that having such a big community of talented developers is a huge plus for WordPress, even if you aren&#8217;t a highly knowledgeable developer, you&#8217;re always going to find someone that can help you out in creating what you want, provided that you have enough curiosity and a drive to learn new things.</p>\n<p><strong>What&#8217;s your least favourite thing about WordPress?</strong><br />\nA difficult question, I&#8217;d say that the default widgets on the dashboard are a nuisance. Yes they can easily be removed, but I&#8217;d prefer if they weren&#8217;t there in the first place. Also it would be nice to have faster image management and insertion when creating new posts and pages.</p>\n<p><strong>What&#8217;s your biggest WordPress related accomplishment?</strong><br />\nDefinitely creating WPMayor and seeing the audience grow from 0 to thousands per month.</p>\n<p>Your affiliate program experiences:</p>\n<p><strong>When did you start participating in affiliate programs?</strong><br />\nSoon after I created WPMayor. I soon realised that I would need some income to justify the huge amount of time I was spending on creating content for the site.</p>\n<p><strong>How do you choose which products you will support as an affiliate?</strong><br />\nI usually come across plugins while working on new projects. If I get excited about a plugin&#8217;s functionality and have the urge to write about it on the blog, I&#8217;ll usually check if there is an affiliate program for it and sign up.</p>\n<p><strong>How much time do you spend on your affiliate efforts?</strong><br />\nIt&#8217;s hard to estimate this because it&#8217;s deeply tied with writing on the WPMayor blog. Curating the blog however takes a big chunk of my time.</p>\n<p><strong>How do you balance your affiliate efforts with other projects you are involved in?</strong><br />\nAffiliate efforts are almost always the result of having discovered a new tool while working on a project, so I&#8217;ll usually take an hour off from a project to write up a blog post about the plugin/theme I&#8217;d like to share with my readers.</p>\n<p><strong>What is the biggest lesson you have learned about being an affiliate?</strong><br />\nYou need to be choosy when selecting affiliate programs. Of course, you should only promote products you believe in and have tested yourself. As a beginner it is tempting to promote all the affiliate programs available, but by time you will see that only a few of them really bring in any real cash. You need to concentrate on a niche and become an expert, only then will your visitors keep turning to you and clicking those affiliate links.</p>\n<p><strong>If you could go back in time and give yourself some advice as a newbie affiliate program participant, what would you say?</strong><br />\nIt would be that of forgetting banners, the results from banners are miserly when compared to a proper product review in the form of a well-thought out article. Takes longer to prepare but the results are much better.</p>\n<p><strong>Any other tips or resources you might recommend to our affiliate program participants?</strong><br />\nFollow other blogs in your niche, they are very good places for discovering new products to promote.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can find out more about the BraveNewCode Affiliate Program <a title=\"Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://www.bravenewcode.com/affiliate-program/\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>View resources for existing Affiliate Program members by logging into our <a title=\"BraveNewCode Support\" href=\"http://www.bravenewcode.com/support/\">support pages</a> and visiting our Affiliate Center.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:118:\"http://www.bravenewcode.com/2012/08/bravenewcode-affiliate-program-tips-an-interview-with-jean-galea-of-wp-mayor/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a: